The nominations for the 2019 Oscars have been released, and three movies in have grabbed the limelight. Roma and The Favourite lead the nomination charts with 10 each, while A Star is Born follows with 8 nominations. Roma is a drama based on director Alfonso Cuarón’s childhood experience of 1970s Mexico City, while The Favourite humorously depicts a power struggle between various women in Queen Anne’s 18th century court. A Star is Born is Bradley Cooper’s directorial debut, and also starred popstar Lady Gaga. The top 2019 Oscar nominations are below. The full list is available here.